result.execSummary:
The defendant James Green Jr was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Drive or Operate Vehicle w/o Consent, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.23(3).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant James Green in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Victim notification has been completed.  Defendant has completed job search at 4 locations since the last court date.
Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing. Court sentenced the defendant to serve 10 months in the House of Correction; credit for 134 days served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 18 MONTHS to the MENTAL HEALTH UNIT  with the following conditions:
-Follow all rules of probation.
-No further violations of the law.
-Mental health assessment and any treatment.
-Absolute sobriety.
-Random urine screens.
--Maintain employment or Obtain GED or HSED.
-Vocational or other skill training,
-Other counseling needs to be determined.
-Perform 20 HOURS of community service at a non-profit agency.
-Provide DNA sample and pay costs.
-Pay victim witness surcharge and all costs, assessments and surcharges.
FAILURE TO PAY ALL FINANCIAL OBLIGATIONS WILL RESULT IN CIVIL JUDGMENT.
Upon successful completion of all terms and conditions of probation the court will authorize expungement.
Court advised the defendant that as a convicted felon he may no longer use or possess any firearms; also he may not vote in any election until his civil rights have been restored.

Defendant James Green in court with attorney Michael Jude.  Randy P. Sitzberger appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant has not provided proof of job search as ordered on the last date.
To the charged offense:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  The Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon not to possess any firearms/body armor.    Court further advised defendant of voting ineligibility.   
Case is adjourned to 3-10-2016 for sentencing.  Defendant is to provide job search information on the next date.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for March 10, 2016 at 08:15 am.

Defendant James Green in court with attorney Daryl A. Kastenson appeared on behalf of attorney Enku Edgar Lin.  Deann L Heard appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Competency hearing does not proceed.  Dr. Collins was called to testify; however, parties held sidebar and defense counsel indicated that defendant believes he is not competent to proceed and concurs with Dr. Collins' findings.  Court released Dr. Collins from testimony on this case.  Based upon conference held with counsel, Dr. Collin's report, and defendant's own assertion of him not being competent, the Court hereby orders proceedings suspended and ordered defendant committed to the Department of Health Services.  Court concurs with referral by Dr. Collins that defendant be evaluated for placement at the Outpatient Competency Remediation Program.  Defendant given 3 days credit.
